      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ALFIE'S PRINCESS (1) has been out of the placings the last couple but was a Grade 5 winner (30.10) three back at Gosford. Better than last run and makes appeal this time. HEY MAC (3) goes very well at this course having never missed the frame including five wins and three placings. Below best last time at Wentworth Park (30.01) in a NG, finishing a 7 length fifth. With even luck and a clean start should be thereabouts. DRINK TWISTIES (8) goes very well here starting 12 times for five wins and two minors. Comes off a (30.02) win last time, scoring by 0.8 lengths in a Grade 5 over 515m at this track. Looks well placed here and among the chances. PITMAN GO QUICK (7) cannot be ruled out.",
